Issues.Body:
```
  Test(() =>
    {
      return "test";
    });

  Test(() =>
  {
    return "test";
  });
```

When I run this code through dotnet-format version '3.3.111304' it will not be reformatted.

I'd expect it to use either the first or the second style ... but not allow both.

The appears to be no `.editorconfig` setting to enforce this.

**Version Used**: VS16.5.2

ReSharper has this. It's a super nice way to be made aware when methods you're already using can now be awaited in `await using` or `await foreach` statements.

```cs
// ℹ Use 'await using'
using var stream = File.Create(path);
```

Result:
```cs
await using var stream = File.Create(path);
```

